{%- comment -%}
  COA batch count — single source of truth.

  Iterates `collections.all.products` and totals every batch present on the
  COA metafield (either `coa.batches` list or single `coa.batch` ref). Used
  by the lab-results dashboard (for the headline batch count) and by any
  homepage stat block that wants to auto-fill the same number.

  Outputs ONLY the integer (no HTML, no whitespace). Callers read it via
  the capture + render pattern:

    {%- capture _batches -%}{% render 'coa-batch-count' %}{%- endcapture -%}
    {%- assign total_batches = _batches | strip | times: 1 -%}

  Note: `collections.all.products` is capped at 50 in a non-paginated for
  loop. If the catalog ever exceeds 50 SKUs with COA data, switch to a
  paginated render or pass a dedicated collection in.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- liquid
  assign total_batches = 0

  for product in collections.all.products
    assign batches = product.metafields.coa.batches.value
    assign single_batch = product.metafields.coa.batch.value

    if batches != blank
      for batch in batches
        assign total_batches = total_batches | plus: 1
      endfor
    elsif single_batch != blank
      assign total_batches = total_batches | plus: 1
    endif
  endfor
-%}
{{- total_batches -}}
